06:13.916 --> 06:15.000
Why?

06:17.127 --> 06:19.004
I was saved.

06:20.881 --> 06:22.674
My body fell to earth,

06:22.674 --> 06:25.636
my bones were broken,

06:25.636 --> 06:28.472
but I asked my Lord for mercy
and He saved me.

06:31.099 --> 06:33.352
Who are you
to overrule the will

06:33.352 --> 06:34.937
of my Lord?

06:40.108 --> 06:42.110
Friends.

06:42.110 --> 06:45.447
We have let a sinner
into our house.

06:49.117 --> 06:52.037
Behold, I will tell you
a mystery.

06:53.664 --> 06:56.542
Not all will sleep,
but all will be chained

06:56.542 --> 06:59.336
in a moment,
in the twinkling of an eye,

06:59.336 --> 07:01.129
at the last trumpet,

07:01.129 --> 07:04.675
for the trumpet will sound
and the dead will be raised,

07:04.675 --> 07:07.845
imperishable,
and we will all be changed!

08:28.425 --> 08:30.135
<i>Local coverage</i>
<i>is what we give you,</i>

08:30.135 --> 08:31.929
<i>it’s what we are.</i>

08:31.929 --> 08:33.304
<i>We’re on the scene</i>
<i>delivering the news</i>

08:33.304 --> 08:34.515
<i>when it happens, as it happens.</i>

08:34.515 --> 08:36.183
<i>We bring you right up close</i>

08:36.183 --> 08:38.227
<i>to events,</i>
<i>local politics and more.</i>

08:38.227 --> 08:40.062
<i>Not to mention</i>
<i>the fast‐changing foliage</i>

08:40.062 --> 08:41.647
- ‐ <i>of the county...</i>
- I can’t believe

08:41.647 --> 08:44.358
you’re going to be
on the show tomorrow.

08:44.358 --> 08:46.026
It’s absurd.

08:46.026 --> 08:49.905
‐ Stay glued.
‐ What is that?

08:49.905 --> 08:53.075
‐ It is a gazebo.
Every revitalized downtown

08:53.075 --> 08:54.868
needs a gazebo.

08:54.868 --> 08:57.746
‐ What’s it for?
‐ I don’t know.

08:57.746 --> 08:59.581
Peaceful contemplation.

08:59.581 --> 09:00.707
The only thing people
contemplate

09:00.707 --> 09:02.292
in this town is suicide.

09:02.292 --> 09:04.878
That’s because
there’s no job base

09:04.878 --> 09:06.421
if you don’t want
to work in a prison.

09:06.421 --> 09:08.173
There’s no local business hub

09:08.173 --> 09:11.343
to encourage social and economic
cross‐pollination.

09:11.343 --> 09:14.805
‐ Yet. That’s phase one.
‐ Wow.

09:14.805 --> 09:17.099
You’re not gonna
say that on TV, right?

09:17.099 --> 09:20.018
‐ What?
‐ Nothing, it’s just that

09:20.018 --> 09:22.396
the camera guy’s
gonna slip into a coma

09:22.396 --> 09:24.565
before you hit phase two.

09:29.361 --> 09:32.072
So, what happens
when I get there?

09:32.072 --> 09:34.658
I just tell ’em
I’m your intern?

09:34.658 --> 09:37.244
Say "executive assistant."

09:40.330 --> 09:42.332
The producer’s name
is Charlene.

09:42.332 --> 09:44.793
She’s gonna meet you
outside the studio.

09:44.793 --> 09:47.212
Please, just try
to avoid potholes.

09:47.212 --> 09:49.923
Why do you care what happens
to this hellscape, anyway?

09:51.633 --> 09:52.885
Just keep it under 40.

10:20.287 --> 10:21.663
Molly Strand.

10:23.040 --> 10:26.210
‐ Yes.
‐ It’s Henry Deaver.

10:26.210 --> 10:27.753
North Prospect?

10:27.753 --> 10:29.922
We were neighbors
back in dinosaur times?

10:29.922 --> 10:33.175
Of course. Henry.

10:33.175 --> 10:35.302
Sorry. I didn’t, um...

10:36.762 --> 10:38.931
‐ It’s been‐‐
‐ A lot of years.

10:38.931 --> 10:40.182
Yeah, I don’t get back much.

10:42.184 --> 10:45.145
Why are‐‐
What are you doing here?

10:45.145 --> 10:46.980
I have a client
over at the prison.

10:46.980 --> 10:49.983
- ‐ A real mess.
<i>- Smells like Cheerios.</i>

10:49.983 --> 10:51.860
<i>Gene Pitney,</i>
<i>"24 Hours From Tulsa."</i>

10:51.860 --> 10:54.238
<i>Does the tape get erased?</i>

10:54.238 --> 10:56.240
<i>Hey, I’m her witness!</i>

10:56.240 --> 10:57.199
Good luck.

10:59.076 --> 11:01.787
Sorry, that was...

11:01.787 --> 11:04.331
Um, yeah,

11:04.331 --> 11:08.210
I would love
to...hear more,

11:08.210 --> 11:11.421
but I have, um,

11:11.421 --> 11:13.048
I have an open house.

11:13.048 --> 11:14.925
Actually,
that’s why I’m here.

11:14.925 --> 11:16.844
I’ve been seeing your signs
all around town.

11:16.844 --> 11:20.264
You want to sell
your mom’s place?

11:20.264 --> 11:24.309
<i>Do you know Alan Pangborn?</i>

11:24.309 --> 11:27.271
‐ ...she needs full‐time care.
‐ Isn’t Sheriff Pangborn‐‐

11:27.271 --> 11:29.398
We’re making some changes.

11:29.398 --> 11:32.568
Um......

11:32.568 --> 11:35.529
‐ I can’t help you.
‐ I’m sorry?

11:37.239 --> 11:41.577
I am‐‐ I’m just
so...overwhelmed here,

11:41.577 --> 11:44.746
I can’t take a new client.

11:44.746 --> 11:48.667
Also, with my parents’ house
being directly across the street

11:48.667 --> 11:51.044
it’s probably
a conflict of interest.

11:51.044 --> 11:54.089
So, um, I can refer you
to someone else.

11:54.089 --> 11:57.843
N‐No. No, I’ll just‐‐

12:06.059 --> 12:08.437
Did I say something wrong?

12:08.437 --> 12:11.106
No. Of course not. You‐‐

12:15.319 --> 12:17.571
It was really good
seeing you.

12:22.701 --> 12:23.994
You too.

12:42.971 --> 12:44.806
Fuck you, Dad.

12:53.232 --> 12:54.316
Hey.

13:03.492 --> 13:06.078
You wanna see my room?

13:06.078 --> 13:08.163
It’s a lot cooler
than it used to be.

13:11.959 --> 13:15.420
I go
to Catholic school now.

13:15.420 --> 13:18.090
‐ My dad made me.
‐ I know.

13:25.472 --> 13:27.391
What are Violent Femmes?

13:27.391 --> 13:29.768
A band.

13:29.768 --> 13:31.979
"Femme" is a girl.

13:31.979 --> 13:33.355
In French.

13:37.234 --> 13:40.404
You know, he’s...

13:40.404 --> 13:42.406
not my real father.

13:42.406 --> 13:44.491
Obviously.

13:46.410 --> 13:48.412
Yeah.

13:50.747 --> 13:53.083
I know what you do
in your room.

13:55.252 --> 13:56.670
Touching your thing.

13:58.380 --> 14:00.757
Feels like...

14:00.757 --> 14:02.467
fireworks.

14:02.467 --> 14:05.971
‐ I ain’t never‐‐
‐ I can’t explain it, but...

14:05.971 --> 14:09.308
I can hear what you’re thinking
and feeling.

14:09.308 --> 14:11.101
When you’re brushing your teeth,

14:11.101 --> 14:12.769
and when
you’re out in the woods,

14:12.769 --> 14:14.813
it’s like
I’m out there with you.

14:17.107 --> 14:18.483
<i>Henry!</i>

14:22.112 --> 14:23.655
<i>Henry, where’d you go?</i>

14:25.490 --> 14:28.744
Son, I want you
back in this house right now.

14:33.373 --> 14:34.833
Henry!

15:01.318 --> 15:04.029
<i>C block,</i>
<i>count time in 30 minutes.</i>

15:30.430 --> 15:32.307
<i>You tell Valerie yet?</i>

15:32.307 --> 15:34.268
<i>Fuck no, I didn’t</i>
<i>tell her about the money.</i>

15:34.268 --> 15:35.894
She’d blow it
on the mortgage.

15:35.894 --> 15:39.731
I’m buyin’ an Xbox
and a pound of weed.

15:39.731 --> 15:43.068
You gonna spend your bonus on
fuckin’ Fischer‐Price Jumperoo?

15:43.068 --> 15:44.903
It’s not a bonus,
it’s a bribe.

15:44.903 --> 15:46.363
So they don’t talk.

15:47.698 --> 15:49.032
About what?

15:51.201 --> 15:52.369
Hey.

15:52.369 --> 15:54.580
Hey! Mickey boy!

15:54.580 --> 15:56.415
‐ Sit the fuck down!
‐ Hey.

15:56.415 --> 15:58.000
You better sit down.

15:58.000 --> 15:59.459
Hey! Sit down!

16:02.212 --> 16:03.505
Sit down.

16:12.222 --> 16:15.100
Look, he’s scheduled a hearing,
he’s gonna get you out,

16:15.100 --> 16:16.977
but you gotta help yourself.

16:18.812 --> 16:20.606
Come on, sit down.

16:25.444 --> 16:29.323
<i>Dude doesn’t eat,</i>
<i>except for Wonder Bread.</i>

16:29.323 --> 16:30.908
Barely sleeps.

16:30.908 --> 16:34.328
Just kinda walks
in these little circles.

16:34.328 --> 16:37.080
Guys watch him on CCTV now.
Nick at Nite.

16:37.080 --> 16:40.459
Some of the COs
call him Nick now.

16:40.459 --> 16:43.128
Like Nick Cage, ’cause
we found him in a cage‐‐

16:43.128 --> 16:44.588
I get it.
‐ Yeah.

16:44.588 --> 16:46.340
Look, I can pull
the security footage.

16:46.340 --> 16:48.091
All right? That would
look real good on CNN.

16:48.091 --> 16:49.593
Let’s hold off on that.

16:49.593 --> 16:51.929
Listen, you gotta
earn his trust.

16:51.929 --> 16:53.931
Get him to tell you
how he got there.

16:53.931 --> 16:55.724
I know how he got there.

16:55.724 --> 16:58.936
Shoulda seen him eye‐fucking
Warden Lacy’s picture.

16:58.936 --> 17:01.772
Nah. I need more.

17:01.772 --> 17:04.525
You gotta tell him,
all right?

17:04.525 --> 17:06.151
<i>Onus probandi,</i> right?

17:06.151 --> 17:08.403
Burden of proof.

17:08.403 --> 17:10.989
Oh, just Wikipedia.

17:12.991 --> 17:14.535
Funny, man, you work
in law enforcement,

17:14.535 --> 17:16.703
nobody knows shit
about the law.

17:16.703 --> 17:18.997
Hey, how long does it take
to become a lawyer, anyway?

17:18.997 --> 17:21.415
I was thinkin’...
I don’t know,

17:21.415 --> 17:23.335
maybe when all this is done,
I go back to school.

17:23.335 --> 17:26.296
You can write me, like,
a recommendation or somethin’.

17:29.675 --> 17:32.553
Uh...yeah. Sure thing.

18:13.802 --> 18:15.304
What the fuck?

18:18.724 --> 18:20.976
Ohh. Really?

18:22.769 --> 18:25.939
I’m tellin’ you,
this town ain’t for shit.

18:25.939 --> 18:29.151
My mom’s boyfriend’s house
got broken into last month.

18:29.151 --> 18:31.987
He came home and two Oxy fiends
were carrying his microwave

18:31.987 --> 18:34.156
out the back door.
It’s probably the same assholes.

18:34.156 --> 18:37.910
‐ Aw. Yeah, maybe.
‐ What’d they take?

18:37.910 --> 18:39.620
I...I don’t know,

18:39.620 --> 18:41.955
I‐I don’t think
anything’s missing.

18:45.083 --> 18:46.960
Huh.

18:46.960 --> 18:49.755
Squatters?
But you didn’t see anybody.

18:49.755 --> 18:51.089
Nope.

18:54.635 --> 18:57.930
Yeah, there’s property damage...

18:57.930 --> 18:59.765
<i>Please hold, ma’am.</i>

18:59.765 --> 19:02.142
You know,
if you hired me full‐time,

19:02.142 --> 19:04.394
I could clean up
this whole place for you.

19:23.247 --> 19:25.916
‐ Cool murder basement.
‐ Mm‐hmm.

19:30.838 --> 19:35.050
Is that...what I think it is?

19:38.804 --> 19:40.514
Oh, shit!

19:40.514 --> 19:42.015
You lived down the street
from him,

19:42.015 --> 19:44.768
so you had like
a front row seat.

19:44.768 --> 19:47.396
Did he do it?
Did he whack his father?

19:47.396 --> 19:49.731
I have such
a crazy day tomorrow.

19:49.731 --> 19:52.609
Um, you know,
I didn’t sleep last night,

19:52.609 --> 19:56.071
and I think right now
I need to focus

19:56.071 --> 19:58.031
on my <i>Local Color</i> presentation.

20:05.706 --> 20:08.125
Thanks for asking, Corey.

20:08.125 --> 20:11.753
Phase one in any
community revitalization...

20:11.753 --> 20:14.506
‐ Phase one...
‐ You gotta know the community.

20:14.506 --> 20:15.632
You’ve gotta know
the community.

20:15.632 --> 20:17.176
Thanks for asking, Corey.

20:17.176 --> 20:19.636
‐ I was born in Maine...
‐ I was born in Maine...

20:19.636 --> 20:21.847
Thanks for asking, Corey.
I was born in Maine...

20:21.847 --> 20:25.684
I am a proud,
fifth‐generation Maineiac.

20:25.684 --> 20:28.687
When I say Castle Rock
has excellent boats‐‐

20:28.687 --> 20:30.522
Don’t say "boats."

20:32.399 --> 20:36.528
OK. Pull it together.
Pull it together.

20:55.756 --> 20:57.174
Shit.

21:01.595 --> 21:03.138
Damnit!

21:13.023 --> 21:15.651
Well, well,
if it isn’t Old Miss Layaway.

21:15.651 --> 21:17.653
You followin’ me now?

21:17.653 --> 21:20.447
I asked around at the school,
and they said to try here.

21:20.447 --> 21:22.241
Said I was your
college counselor.

21:22.241 --> 21:23.200
And how are my chances?

21:25.160 --> 21:27.621
‐ I’ve got money.
‐ Well, looks like we’ve got

21:27.621 --> 21:29.373
a real free market tragedy here.

21:29.373 --> 21:30.707
Demand, but no supply.

21:30.707 --> 21:33.710
‐ What?
‐ My, uh, Gran...

21:33.710 --> 21:36.380
brings the pills down
from Skowhegan,

21:36.380 --> 21:38.715
and her gout took a bad turn,
they have her on bed rest.

21:38.715 --> 21:41.343
So check back next week
or whatever.

21:41.343 --> 21:43.679
I’m having
a really bad fucking day.

21:43.679 --> 21:46.640
This guy I used to know
came back to town,

21:46.640 --> 21:48.934
and it’s really fucking me up.
And...

21:48.934 --> 21:50.936
I’m gonna be on TV
in the morning.

21:50.936 --> 21:52.688
I need my pills.

21:52.688 --> 21:54.898
How many Minions you kill
to make that jacket?

21:54.898 --> 21:55.858
Six.

21:57.484 --> 21:59.820
Listen, if you really
need a fix that bad,

21:59.820 --> 22:01.989
you could always try your luck
at the motor court.

22:01.989 --> 22:04.408
‐ Huh?
‐ Timberland Motor Court.

22:04.408 --> 22:06.034
Ask for Derek.

22:34.271 --> 22:36.899
<i>I can’t explain it.</i>

22:36.899 --> 22:41.111
<i>I can hear what</i>
<i>you’re thinking and feeling.</i>

22:41.111 --> 22:45.115
<i>You know,</i>
<i>he’s not my real father.</i>

22:45.115 --> 22:48.202
<i>Obviously.</i>

22:48.202 --> 22:50.829
<i>The trumpet will sound</i>
<i>and the dead will be raised,</i>

22:50.829 --> 22:52.706
<i>imperishable.</i>

23:22.486 --> 23:23.695
<i>Do you hear it?</i>

23:33.247 --> 23:34.540
Do you hear it now?

23:37.042 --> 23:38.126
<i>Henry!</i>

24:16.540 --> 24:18.834
Hello?

24:26.466 --> 24:27.426
Hi.

24:28.594 --> 24:31.388
‐ Are you OK?
‐ Yes.

24:32.931 --> 24:35.267
Where’s Derek?

24:40.105 --> 24:41.356
OK.

24:44.151 --> 24:47.070
<i>Bring her up here, Bailiff.</i>
<i>Immediately.</i>

24:47.070 --> 24:50.532
<i>We don’t have to help?</i>

24:50.532 --> 24:52.951
<i>You have to follow</i>
<i>the court’s rules.</i>

24:52.951 --> 24:55.204
<i>That means I am to escort you.</i>

24:55.204 --> 24:58.248
<i>Sit still, witness.</i>

24:58.248 --> 25:00.417
<i>You have to be sworn in first.</i>

25:00.417 --> 25:02.085
<i>Do you swear</i>
<i>to tell the truth,</i>

25:02.085 --> 25:03.629
<i>the whole truth,</i>
<i>and nothing but the truth?</i>

25:03.629 --> 25:05.506
<i>- Yes.</i>
<i>- Tell the court‐‐</i>

25:05.506 --> 25:07.174
<i>what did you see?</i>

25:07.174 --> 25:09.301
<i>Her sneaker was</i>
<i>full of blood.</i>

25:09.301 --> 25:10.886
<i>What was the cause of death?</i>

25:10.886 --> 25:12.513
<i>Holes punched</i>
<i>in her stomach.</i>

25:12.513 --> 25:13.722
<i>Her head was bashed</i>

25:13.722 --> 25:15.265
against a rock quarry stone.

25:15.265 --> 25:18.352
And in your professional
opinion, Coroner,

25:18.352 --> 25:20.562
how would you categorize
this murder?

25:20.562 --> 25:22.898
Was it a crime of passion?

25:22.898 --> 25:25.067
The wounds on the body
were deep and red,

25:25.067 --> 25:28.237
so we believe the murderer
was someone she knew.

25:28.237 --> 25:30.364
Could it have been someone
in her family?

25:30.364 --> 25:31.698
Maybe.

25:31.698 --> 25:33.992
We can test the blood for that.

25:33.992 --> 25:36.662
Or maybe it was her best friend.

25:49.341 --> 25:52.135
I’m‐‐
I’m looking for someone.

25:52.135 --> 25:54.805
Go on with your testimony.

25:54.805 --> 25:57.307
I don’t care about your‐‐
your game, OK?

25:57.307 --> 26:00.269
‐ Sit down.
‐ Just tell Derek I’m here.

26:00.269 --> 26:02.229
If you want
what you came for,

26:02.229 --> 26:04.398
then sit down!

26:08.944 --> 26:12.072
I won’t tolerate
any further interruptions.

26:12.072 --> 26:16.118
I will have order
in this court.

26:16.118 --> 26:18.954
- ‐ The court appreciates...
- Where are your parents?

26:18.954 --> 26:20.747
They’re out drunk.

26:20.747 --> 26:22.457
Our moms are out drunk,

26:22.457 --> 26:24.293
but our daddies
are at Shawshank.

26:24.293 --> 26:25.961
- ‐ All of them?
- You understand

26:25.961 --> 26:27.421
that you are on trial
for murder?

